Class CourseListTest

  • java.lang.Object
    • CourseListTest

  • public class CourseListTest
extends java.lang.Object
    Test Class of the CourseList class. CourseList is a custom linked list that is tuned for holding Courses in them and one link is for the next element in the list and the other link is for the next element that is in the same semester as the current element.
    Author:
    Yasir

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Concrete Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void add()
      Tries to add an element to the list and controls the size and the first element of the list and makes sure that the size is 1 and the first element is the added one.
      void get()
      Tries to get an element with its index and compares it with the element added at that index.
      void next()
      Tries to move the current element of the list to its next value and compares the resulting value with the element that is added after first element.
      void nextInSemester()
      Tries to move the current element of the list to its nextInSemester value and compares the resulting value with the actual element that is in the same semester and next.
      void remove()
      Tries to remove 3 elements and compares first index with the expected element.
      void size()
      Tries to add 3 elements and compares the return value of size method with integer 3.
